{"type":"message","id":"c51b5c16","parentId":"4d082ddf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:48:51.317Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize this pulse cycle concisely.","thinkingSignature":"6a0381df910cac3c5f8bb8e0d485d96a2704b7a3a7c13e16a1a03a3c70b2af54"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-24 14:48 UTC**\n\n**What happened:**\n- The sandbox continued CFI Compression research. The previous pulse identified that binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60) are **too aggressive** — they flag \"constant format\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) as causal when they're just template artifacts.\n- This pulse advanced the synthesis: the insight is that a **hybrid scoring formula** `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` should separate constant-format noise from true research signals.\n- A mutation was applied to `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` — updating the \"Pending\" section into a concrete experiment plan with the hybrid formula and a planned `hybrid_scoring_analysis.ps1` script.\n\n**Result:** 7 files changed, 185 insertions, 41 deletions. One mutation committed, one new proposed mutation pending for the next pulse.\n\n**Status:** Active research cycle — CFI compression Phase 1 ongoing, next step is running the hybrid scoring experiment on 200 pulses."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3010,"output":254,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15509,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774378121306}}
